Sync="TRUE">en</langdata>       <abstract>The AGIO is responding to a request from the GIS Board to coordinate lidar data development in an effort to reduce duplication of effort. The AGIO has been coordinating with US Army COE, FEMA, NRCS and USGS to determine where publically funded lidar exist within the state of Arkansas.  This file represents geographic footprints that detail the availability of lidar data and the points of contact. Note: Availabity means complete, contracted or planned for the purpose of this effort.</abstract>       <purpose>Please let us know if you are aware of lidar projects that have been completed, are contracted, or planned. We will continue to update this file as projects come to our attention. </purpose>     </descript>     <citation>       <citeinfo>         <origin>Arkansas Geographic Information Office</origin>
